This Thursday from 6-9pm myself and @triple_js_hobby_works are putting together a RC “come drive” evening for our veterans and their families downstairs at the Egan Center. Had an absolute blast at the Toys for Tots race @thunder_alley_rc_raceway this past weekend racing under the @wb_factoryracing tent. Such a rad track! This was my 1st out of state rc race of any kind and it definitely didn’t disappoint. The new @teamassociatedrc cars are pretty sweet and I got to drive Nitro for the 1st time. In standard form I expected a lot and the results were a bit disappointing but definitely had pace at times. Overall learned lots and got to meet a bunch of really cool people. RC is such a great community. So now we have a little tuning to do to get the new cars dialed and will definitely be in the mix at the next one! A huge thank you to @nickwautlet and @caitydee14 for the hospitality. You guys rock. #wbractoryracing #walliebuilds🔧 #reamtekin #rawspeed #protekrc #pt11

Its no big secret that I am pretty passionate about a few things in this crazy life. Snowmobiles, fishing, rc, family and I have tailored my veteran events to many of these things to share passions with our nation’s finest humans. One of the greatest opportunities this afford me is to be able to take my Vietnam Veteran dad fishing once in a while. We just finished up another all time trip chasing the mightiest of trout with @caylen_phegley . Its hard to put into words how much these trips mean. To be able to do something for not only a fella that selflessly served his county but helped shape me into the man I am today is pretty special…even if he is a giant smartass 😂. Never a dull moment on the water thats for sure. #veteran #warriorride #steelhead

So its taken a few days for this to completely sink it. Any trout fisherman, quite literally, dreams about hooking into a 20lb steelhead. They are like the unicorn of fresh water fishing. Ive been chasing these monsters longer than I can remember. After hundreds of thousands of casts, thousands of miles flown/driven and hundreds of days spent trying to check this box, it finally happened. Huge thank you to @caylen_phegley for putting me on this monster and my dad for screwing up his cast so I could get to him 1st 😂 Such an epic battle ensued to finally be able to shake hands with this dinosaur. Amazing. #pt11 #steelhead #fishing #40”x21” #22lbs

Well #DNC is over. Man what a crazy 5 days. The big track was unreal but Mother Nature wasn’t having it and Joey and @thedirtracing crew were able to put together an impromptu smaller track under the roof next door. Impressive accomplishment. Definitely threw a wrench in the program as it was like starting from scratch with set ups. Had some crazy outside my control luck with qualifying in ebuggy and nitro buggy so had to dance in the lower mains. Truck was good and I qualified straight to the main in Int and missed the bump by 0.2 seconds in 40+. Overall we moved the needle in the right direction and getting closer to having cars that are really good. Had a blast with the @wallie_builds crew and met lots of new great humans. Doesn’t seem to matter what kind of level of motor sports it is, its always made up of great folks. Looking forward to the next one! #pt11 #wbfactory #teamtekin #protekrc #1upracing #weareae

On this episode of The Young Guides Podcast, Keaton and Kyle chat with Paul Thacker. Paul is is a wealth of knowledge in all things fishing Alaska and draws from his experiences on various destination fisheries. Paul talks about his story racing in the X Games and chasing world record snow machine jumps. They chat about how Paul’s perspective on life changed after a tragic snow machine accident. Get to know more about Paul, his accomplishments, how he gives back to the community and his determination to keep grinding everyday.

For those of you that might be interested we have started the offroad rc racing for the summer at the track down at the south Anchorage ball fields off Abbott rd. We are racing Tuesday and Thursday nights. Tuesdays are our points series races and Thursday is a more laid back non points just for fun night. We are hoping to use that as a good time to bring out new folks that are interested in racing but havent had much track time. So if you are interested in coming out please hit me up or reach out to Triple J's Hobby Works or AROARA RC Racing Any of us can answer any questions you might have, get you lined out on what you will need to come rip with us and probably have cars that you could even demo a little. So bring friends, family members, boyfriend, girlfriends or whomever and come enjoy some scaled down supercross style rc racing.

Well after nearly two seasons of planning we got rc racing back @officialalaskastatefair !! 
Its been over 30 years since the last races and never has there been anything like what we pulled off. The last Monster Truck show started at 4pm Sun afternoon and by 10am Morning morning we had an unreal race track. The dirt work done by @westbroscontractorsltd was a straight up miracle. The amount of volunteer help we had working through the night was amazing and mother nature gave the rain a rest, replacing it with sunshine and the nicest day of fall so far. Such an incredible day of racing! Big air, tight battles, gnarly crashes and a rowdy crowd made for one of the most fun times in memory. We created some hype, excitement about rc in Alaska and I cant wait to see what next year brings! Special thanks to everyone that helped contribute! #pt11 #akstatefair #drivetlr #teamtekin #rawspeed
#protekrc #boomrc

Some of you might remember my “no handed” backflip at Xgames in 2010. Not just no handed in the air, no handed the whole time. We took an rc servo and rigged it to my throttle and I actually flipped without touching the bars at all. No handed on the run in, the air and the landing. The 1st attempt I landed about 3 inches short, bucked a little and I rolled off the side as I went down the landing, second attempt I threw my head back and rotated way to fast so I had to come back to the bars to hit the brakes but landed and rode it out. For some reason it was completely scrubbed from the internet about a week after the event. Probably didn’t wwnt anyone else attempting that silliness again! 😂 #pt11 #polaris #monsterenergy #xgames

To all those that have served, thank you for your service. #warriorride #veterans #veteransday

In 2011 I sat in a room and told my story about my injury and subsequent recovery in hopes it might help our nations veterans in their journey through recovery. Somewhere in that 3 hours it donned on me that I could potentially have a unique perspective and if I could tell that story to more veterans maybe I could help even more. Then I thought “why not take the healing powers of backcountry snowmobiling and add that to it as well. That 1st year I was able to make a single event happen. Since then with the help of companies like 
@monsterenergy @polarissnow @straightline_performance @flyracingusa and many others, we  do several events annually, have had hundreds come through the programs and have motivated veterans that have been on these rides to start their own foundations supporting our nation’s finest. Its been one of the most rewarding things Ive ever been a part of. I feel its just a small thing to give back for the sacrifices given. Happy Veterans Day and thank you all for your service. #warriorrides #veterans #usa

Well the race weekend is over and I had an absolute blast in AZ this weekend attending the US Open Fuel Champs at Adobe MT RC. What a rad spot! Tim Lime and the crew are really building something awesome. The hospitality was top notch. 

As far as the racing went it was pretty decent. Haven’t gotten to run much offroad at home these days because of winter and snow and all that, so I just wanted to make A Mains in my 3 classes. Ended up in all 3 A’s, went P6 in Truck, P4 in ebuggy and P7 in nitro buggy. Something to build on for the next one. 
Big thanks to @wallie_builds crew for bringing out the goods and all the help. @nickwautlet @agavelouis and @caitydee14 are the best team and @arrowhead_pat for doing a little of everything!
